<P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#000000><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=chiriko>chiriko</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Forum Apprentice</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>5/4/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>2:06:08 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Anyone still enjoy playing their wizard?</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">I still enjoy playing my wizard alot, even if I am only lvl 31. When I started playing everquest way back in the day, I started with a cleric, and yes, life is pretty easy for a cleric. my cleric is lvl 54 now and has no trouble finding a group, which is nice, but a cleric is a one trick pony. You find a group or you don't do anything. and even once you're in a group, you sit and med, maybe stun if you're lucky enough to have clarity.<br>
<br>
A wizard on the other hand has options, ones I think many people are apt to over look in their rush to point out the (many) flaws of the class. Ports *are* a huge advantage, if I can't get a group in one area, and I can bounce off somewhere else and try again, work on my trade skills or start a quest. with out ports, if you're deep in kunark somewhere, its often too much trouble to leave the area you're in because it can take so long to get back. With my cleric I've gone litterally months without ever making it to the bank.<br>
<br>
But besides ports, there's a wide veriety of ways for a wizard to gain expirence... they can solo very effectively, both quad and single kiting. and in a group they can play many different roles, snaring, nuking, stunning.. its that that versitility, even in a class that's so specialized, that keeps the wizard intresting for me.<br>
<br>
-Chiriko, lvl 31 wizard, Innoruuk</font><P><P><i></i></TD></TR><TR BGCOLOR=#33333><TD NOWRAP width=20% valign=top align=left><B><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=2><A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uincinerategnomewiz.showPublicProfile?language=EN>IncinErate GnomeWiz</A></FONT></B><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>Forum Apprentice</FONT><BR><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>(</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>5/4/01</FONT> <FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1 COLOR=#ffffff>3:31:38 pm</FONT><FONT FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/legionofapathy/members/incin.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Re: Anyone still enjoy playing their wizard?</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Only when I'm dropping hordes of monsters and newbie jaws with AE's.<br>
